docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When Shy Rodriguez heard about one of the hottest trends in education during the pandemic — “learning pods,” where parents hire teachers for small-group, in-home instruction — she knew immediately it was something she could never afford for her sons.

docs.abstract: The civil rights leader answered questions about his experience in the struggle for equal rights and the current state of the nation.
docs.snippet: The civil rights leader answered questions about his experience in the struggle for equal rights and the current state of the nation.
docs.lead_paragraph: In an Op-Ed article this week, the Rev. Jesse Jackson wrote about the need to remember the Rev. Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. as a radical, ecumenical, antiwar, pro-immigrant and scholarly champion of the poor. Readers shared their own reminiscences about Dr. King and their thoughts on the changes in the country since his assassination 50 years ago. Here are some of their comments and Mr. Jackson’s responses. — The Editors

headline.main: Jesse Jackson on Race Relations, Trump and the Right to Vote

docs.abstract: The pandemic has given the famous stretch of Midtown, long a hub and destination for all things jewelry, its share of troubles.
docs.snippet: The pandemic has given the famous stretch of Midtown, long a hub and destination for all things jewelry, its share of troubles.
docs.lead_paragraph: In Manhattan’s diamond district, Mascha Seiden is known as the queen of 47th Street, at least the stretch of it between Fifth Avenue and Avenue of the Americas. For more than 50 years, she has been inspecting pieces of jewelry and chatting with customers from behind the counter of her store, Paul Seiden Jewelers. These days, though, fewer customers have been coming in.

headline.print_headline: Under Pressure: Diamond District Defies Adversity

docs.abstract: As President Biden calls for unity and calmer rhetoric, his presidency began with burned flags and federal agents deployed once again into the streets.
docs.snippet: As President Biden calls for unity and calmer rhetoric, his presidency began with burned flags and federal agents deployed once again into the streets.
docs.lead_paragraph: PORTLAND, Ore. — In the hours after President Biden’s inauguration on Wednesday, hundreds of people gathered for a series of events across the liberal city of Portland, Ore. — not to celebrate, but to mobilize for the struggles to come.

headline.main: They’re Breaking Glass and Criticizing Biden. From the Left.
headline.print_headline: Federal Agents Tear-Gas Demonstrators in Portland After Biden Inauguration

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The first time defenders of Donald J. Trump came for Representative Liz Cheney, for the offense of having voted to impeach him, fellow Republicans closed ranks to save her leadership post, with Representative Kevin McCarthy boasting that their “big tent” party had enough room for both the former president and a stalwart critic.

headline.main: House Republicans Have Had Enough of Liz Cheney’s Truth-Telling
